    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho tāyano devaputto purāṇatitthakaro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, the glorious god Tāyana, formerly a religious founder, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:1.3",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho tāyano devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:2.1",
          "pli": "“Chinda sotaṃ parakkamma, ",
          "en": "“Strive and cut the stream! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:2.2",
          "pli": "kāme panuda brāhmaṇa; ",
          "en": "Dispel sensual pleasures, brahmin. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:2.3",
          "pli": "Nappahāya munī kāme, ",
          "en": "A sage who doesn’t give up sensual pleasures "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:2.4",
          "pli": "nekattamupapajjati. ",
          "en": "is not reborn in a unified state. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:3.1",
          "pli": "Kayirā ce kayirāthenaṃ, ",
          "en": "If one is to do what should be done, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:3.2",
          "pli": "daḷhamenaṃ parakkame; ",
          "en": "one should staunchly strive. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:3.3",
          "pli": "Sithilo hi paribbājo, ",
          "en": "For the life gone forth when laxly led "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:3.4",
          "pli": "bhiyyo ākirate rajaṃ. ",
          "en": "just stirs up dust all the more. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:4.1",
          "pli": "Akataṃ dukkaṭaṃ seyyo, ",
          "en": "It’s better to leave a bad deed undone—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:4.2",
          "pli": "pacchā tapati dukkaṭaṃ; ",
          "en": "later you burn for that misdeed. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:4.3",
          "pli": "Katañca sukataṃ seyyo, ",
          "en": "It’s better to do a good deed, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:4.4",
          "pli": "yaṃ katvā nānutappati. ",
          "en": "after which you’ll not regret. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:5.1",
          "pli": "Kuso yathā duggahito, ",
          "en": "When kusa grass is wrongly grasped "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:5.2",
          "pli": "hatthamevānukantati; ",
          "en": "it only cuts the hand. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:5.3",
          "pli": "Sāmaññaṃ dupparāmaṭṭhaṃ, ",
          "en": "So too, the ascetic life, when wrongly taken, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:5.4",
          "pli": "nirayāyūpakaḍḍhati. ",
          "en": "drags you to hell. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:6.1",
          "pli": "Yaṃ kiñci sithilaṃ kammaṃ, ",
          "en": "Any lax act, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:6.2",
          "pli": "saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṃ vataṃ; ",
          "en": "any corrupt observance, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:6.3",
          "pli": "Saṅkassaraṃ brahmacariyaṃ, ",
          "en": "or suspicious spiritual life, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:6.4",
          "pli": "na taṃ hoti mahapphalan”ti. ",
          "en": "is not very fruitful.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:7.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca tāyano devaputto; ",
          "en": "That’s what the god Tāyana said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:7.2",
          "pli": "idaṃ vatvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyīti. ",
          "en": "Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:8.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha told the mendicants all that had happened. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:8.2",
          "pli": "“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ tāyano nāma devaputto purāṇatitthakaro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, tonight, the glorious god Tāyana, formerly a religious founder, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:8.3",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, tāyano devaputto mama santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited these verses in my presence.” The Buddha repeated the verses in full, adding: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:9.1",
          "pli": "‘Chinda sotaṃ parakkamma, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:9.2",
          "pli": "kāme panuda brāhmaṇa; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:9.3",
          "pli": "Nappahāya munī kāme, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:9.4",
          "pli": "nekattamupapajjati. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:10.1",
          "pli": "Kayirā ce kayirāthenaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:10.2",
          "pli": "daḷhamenaṃ parakkame; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:10.3",
          "pli": "Sithilo hi paribbājo, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:10.4",
          "pli": "bhiyyo ākirate rajaṃ. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:11.1",
          "pli": "Akataṃ dukkaṭaṃ seyyo, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:11.2",
          "pli": "pacchā tapati dukkaṭaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:11.3",
          "pli": "Katañca sukataṃ seyyo, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:11.4",
          "pli": "yaṃ katvā nānutappati. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:12.1",
          "pli": "Kuso yathā duggahito, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:12.2",
          "pli": "hatthamevānukantati; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:12.3",
          "pli": "Sāmaññaṃ dupparāmaṭṭhaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:12.4",
          "pli": "nirayāyūpakaḍḍhati. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:13.1",
          "pli": "Yaṃ kiñci sithilaṃ kammaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:13.2",
          "pli": "saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṃ vataṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:13.3",
          "pli": "Saṅkassaraṃ brahmacariyaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:13.4",
          "pli": "na taṃ hoti mahapphalan’ti. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:14.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, tāyano devaputto, idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. ",
          "en": "“That’s what the god Tāyana said. Then he bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right side, before vanishing right there. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:14.2",
          "pli": "Uggaṇhātha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā; ",
          "en": "Mendicants, learn the verses of Tāyana! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:14.3",
          "pli": "pariyāpuṇātha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā; ",
          "en": "Memorize the verses of Tāyana! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:14.4",
          "pli": "dhāretha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā. ",
          "en": "Remember the verses of Tāyana! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.8:14.5",
          "pli": "Atthasaṃhitā, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā ādibrahmacariyikā”ti. ",
          "en": "These verses are beneficial and relate to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.”"
        }
      ],
